# Searching

Atlas CertOps supports global search.

Searchable fields include:

Certificate Name

Certificate ID

Owner

Department

Vendor

Certification Type

Asset

Equipment

Notes

Tags

Partial matches are supported.

Filters may be combined.

Example:

Owner = Engineering

Status = Expiring

Department = Operations

---

# Creating a Certificate

Navigate:

Certificates → New Certificate

Complete all required fields.

Required fields include:

Certificate Name

Certificate Type

Owner

Issue Date

Expiration Date

Approver

Department

Optional fields include:

Serial Number

Vendor

Reference Number

Cost Center

Comments

Supporting Documents

Select Save.

The certificate immediately becomes part of the compliance inventory.

---

# Editing Certificates

Open the certificate.

Select Edit.

Modify desired fields.

Select Save.

All changes are recorded in the Audit Log.

---

# Deleting Certificates

Deletion permissions are limited to Administrators.

Deleted records are soft deleted.

Retention policies determine final removal.

Deletion events are permanently logged.

---

# Uploading Supporting Documents

Documents may include:

PDF

Images

Word Documents

Spreadsheets

Certificates

Licenses

Training Records

Maximum file size is configurable by your organization.

Uploaded files are encrypted during transmission and storage.

---

# Renewing Certificates

Open the certificate.

Select Renew.

Update:

Issue Date

Expiration Date

Renewal Documentation

Comments

Submit.

Depending on organizational policy:

Renewal may require approval.

